    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "Elsonâ€™s test: bend PIP 90 deg over edge of table, extend middle phalanx against resistance. Should have weak PIP extension and DIP goes rigid as lateral bands have to work.\nPositive test indicated rupture of central tendon slip.\nXR to assess for avulsion\nfracture of middle phalanx",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "fracture of middle phalanx",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Phalynx_fracture"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "If open or with displaced avulsion fracture: operative repair\nClosed: splint in extension (Both DIP and PIP) for up to 6 weeks, refer to hand surgeon. NO flexion of DP permitted for duration of splinting, including during cleaning. Repair extensor tendon if injured.",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Disposition": {
      "text": "Hand specialist follow up if closed injury\nImmediate consult if deformity is caused by open injury",
      "subsections": {},
